						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 7 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Perumānaḍigaḷ at Tirunalakkuṉṟam in Kuṉṟiyūr-nāḍu by (a lady) <hi rend="bold">Udaiyaṉ Kalimadi</hi> on behalf of her (deceased ?) son <hi rend="bold">Viḻuppēraiyar Vēḷāṉ Pugaḻaṉ of Maṇṇaikkuḍi.</hi> This might be an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi> (No. 69, <hi rend="italic">Pud. Ins.</hi> Texts).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
